Description:
AN IMPRESSIVE DENNIS FAMILY HOME WITH DUAL ACCESS AND STYLE.
Take the time to view this great home, with style and subtle colours combined to make this 2018 build sparkle. Light and bright throughout add to the warm appeal of this home. The open plan living space allows for dining, living and the best kitchen with butlers pantry and so well equipped , all opening to the undercover alfresco area where entertaining is easy. A second living room provides more space to relax. Four bedrooms, the main is really big enough for a retreat, has WIR and ensuite, the remaining three are all generous and all have WIR plus study too. Central bathroom with separate toilet and powder room, laundry to complete.
Features of the home include eco central heating and cooling, stone benches, dishwasher, loads of storage quality appliances and fittings as well as a double garage with internal access and another access with second garage./big shed.
Heritage Mews is a prime spot on the edge of the residential area with bush walks and bike rides all the way to Queenscliff along the Rail Trail and Lake Lorne for that daily walk ....no car, just around the corner. Schools are a short walk as well as access to the Village shops and all amenities. Take the stress out of building, make an appointment now.

Description:
LARGE FAMILY HOME, PRIZED LOCATION
Properties compising this land area and location are sought after and quickly snapped up ! In close proximity to quality educational facilities and an expansive Drysdale shopping centre but with the space afforded a rural location. This spacious property has plenty of room for the big shed, tennis court and pool.
The home is of solid construction and just waiting to have a touch of modern flair added. Five generous-sized bedrooms - three upstairs and two downstairs. This home comes with two complete kitchens - downstairs has recently been renovated - allowing the opportunity for parents or older children to have their private living space. The living areas are generous and will accommodate any large family. Access to upstairs can be gained via internal and external stairs.
Features of the property include renovated laundry with plenty of storage, as-new gas HWS, massive under cover outdoor entertaining space, double garage and beautiful garden areas.

Description:
An Exceptional and Rare Block of Land in Central Drysdale
ON The Market
An outstanding opportunity presents itself to build in the heart of the ever so charming Drysdale. Located just off High Street this rare and well connected location has it all! Within easy reach to everything - the town centre, schools, cafés, walking tracks, medical facilities.... the list goes on! With all you could want and need so close, you can leave the car at home.
With the land due for titling due by the end of July 2020, now is the perfect time to get your plans ready to bring your dream home to life! It is an ideal time to take advantage of the $25,000 Government incentive under the new Job Builder scheme. And for first home buyers it is even more attractive with the potential to get up to $45,000 in grants and stamp duty savings. Amazing!
Is this idyllic location you will love being surrounded by the already established homes and enjoy the lifestyle benefits of living on the beautiful Bellarine! Secure this approximately 495m2 piece of land and begin your property building journey today!
The Bellarine peninsula is renowned for the blissful, outdoor lifestyle. Central to bay side beaches, local wineries, and great fishing spots. The Port Phillip Ferry sails daily from Portarlington and South Bank if you fancy a day trip to the city. Combine this with the new Drysdale bypass to improve ease of commuting from the Bellarine, and creating countless benefits to locals and visitors.
This will fly!!! Don't you be the one to miss out..
Roncon Real Estate Always ON!

Description:
"JUST LOVE MY HOME AND STUDIO "
Central position, stroll to the village centre, coffee, shop, walk and enjoy all the parklands. Absolutely nothing to do, just perfect ! The spacious living room is light and bright, has adjacent kitchen with doors opening to a sunroom area/library, all overlooking the garden haven, vibrant colours and produce. Two queen bedrooms with BIR'S, central bathroom, laundry and powder room. Features include shutters, walk in pantry, dishwasher, split system, bosch wall oven, fans, three watertanks, two sheds (big and small) plus manufactured timber flooring. Carport behind secure gates with plenty of room for more standing in driveway off road. The freestanding studio allows for flexible use... third bedroom, work room or home office. Take the time to view all that is here, downsize with ease, great first time buy or astute investment opportunity.

Description:
The family home with it all
Plenty of space for the whole family and all of your friends makes this one property you don't want to miss in Drysdale's beautiful Central Walk.
Spread out across THREE whole living areas; a lounge at the rear of the property, east facing sitting room and grand open plan kitchen, dining and living area so no matter what, everyone can watch their favourite programs in peace.
Open plan kitchen, dining, lounge is sure to impress. Kitchen full to the guts with 900mm five burner gas cooktop, stainless steel wall oven, dishwasher and plenty of drawer and pantry space.
If outdoor entertaining is your life, you'll love this too; the entire outdoor of the home is undercover so you can have your pool table and barbecues set up year round for all of your friends to come around and enjoy no matter the weather, don't forget the steam sauna either!
The master bedroom features views onto the fully landscaped garden and an enormous walk-through robe and ensuite to match. The fully-optioned ensuite is closer to being it's own full bathroom with extra large shower, double vanity and toilet.
Second, third and fourth bedrooms all have built-in robes and will fit anywhere from a single to king size bed.
Extra large 6m by 7m garage with drive through access means you won't bang your car doors and you've got plenty of room for storing that camping gear or the boat.
Additional features include refrigerated air conditioning and ducted heating, Ethernet connections in most rooms, alarm system, CrimSafe security door, plantation blinds in each room and flood lights in the backyard all on a 537sqm block.

Description:
Immaculately Presented Home in Central Walk Estate
The Feel:
Situated in sought-after Central Walk, this 3-bedroom home presents as new. Immaculately presented, the floorplan provides open plan living & a protected outdoor lifestyle zone, capitalising on the sunny north orientation with a private outdoor therapeutic spa. Ziptrack café blinds to the undercover deck promise year-round entertaining, while a luxurious master wing & 2 versatile bedrooms/study will suit first home buyers or downsizers. High quality appliances, stone benches & a WIP make cooking a breeze. Parks & wetlands provide a lovely setting, conveniently located under 1km from the local school & shops.
The Facts:
-Quality custom-built brick veneer & linear board residence, built by Simonds Homes
-Highly regarded Central Walk estate boasts stunning parklands
-Inviting pathway to private entry with oak timber laminate floors throughout & carpet to bedrooms
-Open plan living, meals & kitchen features glass pendant lights
-Modern kitchen with clean lines, caesarstone island bench, picture window & WIP
-Stainless steel appliances (Technika 900mm oven & gas hob, DeLonghi DW)
-Sunny living & meals area connects seamlessly to outdoor area via stacker sliding doors
-Undercover alfresco area with merbau deck & Ziptrack café blinds for year-round entertaining
-Leisurescape Sorrento 3 hydro therapy spa with 51 jets & side by side reclining lounges
-Ducted heating/evaporative cooling throughout, & ceiling fans in all rooms
-Spacious Master wing with Queen size bedroom, TV point & WIR
-Luxury en-suite with large shower, vanity, Lucci 3in1 bathroom heater & WC
-2 more bedrooms with BIRs & flexibility to set up a home office
-Central bathroom (vanity, XL tub, shower, Lucci 3in1 bathroom heater, sep WC)
-5.5kw solar panel system, continuous flow gas hot water system
-Fully fenced low maintenance landscaped garden with synthetic turf at rear
-Exposed aggregate driveway to RC SLUG with internal & rear path access
-3mins drive to cafes & shops, 1km to Drysdale PS, 600m to Rail Trail
The Owner Loves.
I love the convenience of this location and that I always feel like Im on a holiday... Theres nothing better than relaxing in the spa every night, with the therapeutic benefits of hydro therapy jets.

Description:
Best Of Both Worlds - Tender Now Closed.
Occupying an expansive 2+ acres (9,967 sqm), this elevated site offers the best of rural living only moments from the Drysdale town centre. Undulating with established foliage at times this location feels like a world away from the city grind. It is offered with a home that may present an opportunity for a builder or a do it yourself renovator who has the skill and knowledge to salvage the home and bringing it back to life, or simply start again with a blank canvas and build your dream home. Just a few moments to Lake Lorne and parkland, a safe ride to the Pony Club, or along the Rail Trail plus St Thomas Catholic Primary School, Saint Ignatius College Geelong and literally a 6 minute drive to the town centre and around 25 minutes to the Geelong CBD. On the beautiful Bellarine this is the change you have been looking for.
**Now known as 1-29 McKiernan Street, Drysdale.
Tender Now Closed.
Tender closing 10th September 2020 at 4:00 PM.

Description:
Family Appeal with Amazing Future Prospects!
Not every day does an opportunity like 20 Kimberley Avenue present itself where the location is everything and the astute buyer will enjoy the proximity and the convenience of being able to walk to the vibrant Drysdale Shopping Precinct.
This versatile property, totalling 658sqm (approx.), makes its return to the market for the first time in over 30 years. This home would be perfect for those looking to break into the first home buyer market or those looking to renovate and invest. With its blank palette and the right amount of imagination this home could be transformed into something special.
Featuring a classic floor-plan design with 3 bedrooms, 2 spacious living areas and a practical kitchen, this home will not disappoint. A side access driveway has enough space to accommodate a boat and a caravan. The backyard features established citrus trees and other various fruit trees and plenty of water storage options (3 x 8000 litre water tanks).
To further enhance this irresistible opportunity, a short stroll sees you in the heart of Central Drysdale's vibrancy where you will find cafes, restaurants, shopping options and a vast array of high-quality schools close by. Award winning wineries and lifestyles pursuits that the Bellarine Peninsula is renowned for are only minutes' drive from this fabulous location. Opportunities like this do not come around very often, so please feel free to call me anytime to arrange an inspection at this property.

Description:
The Jewel Of Drysdale!
This beautifully appointed residence is sure to delight prospective buyers with an uncompromising buying brief. A custom build of the highest calibre is complemented by an enviable location; the wonderful village lifestyle of the Drysdale township is literally a stones throw from your doorstep. Light filled living zones, impressive high ceilings and myriad of custom features provide just a hint to what is sure to be a memorable inspection.
2 bedrooms of grand proportions; both complete with built-in robes and wonderful outlook to delightful garden settings
The primary living zone consists of an open plan kitchen/dining/lounge. Expansive windows and a northerly aspect promote an abundance of natural light. A glass sliding door creates as seamless connection to a sheltered courtyard; a tranquil spot to take in a morning coffee 'or' an evening glass of one of your favourite local award winning wineries.
The kitchen serves up a great user friendly space; expansive benchtops, updated Westinghouse and Bosch appliances and excellent storage solutions.
A modernised bathroom is spacious; complete with bath, shower and a skylight yet again ensures a light and bright experience.
All the modern comforts; ducted heating, split system cooling, ceiling fans and many more fine features to be discovered on further inspection
The garage has remote controlled access and rear pedestrian access; the gable roof creates further storage solutions.
The Bellarine Peninsula is a thriving market place; award winning wineries, a vibrant café and restaurant scene, fully equipped medical services, beautiful parklands and the tranquillity of the 'sea change' are all at 'arms reach' if you are lucky enough to secure the charming 2/15 Carolanne Drive, Drysdale

Description:
Retirement Awaits You!
Due to COVID-19 Regulations, Inspections are by appointment only. Wearing of masks and social distancing apply. Contact agent to organise a time.
This well priced and spacious 2 bedroom unit is situated in the Drysdale Retirement Village located in the heart of Drysdale and just a short stroll to all that this wonderful part of the world offers. Alternatively the bus stop is located for convenience at the front of the village. This unit was constructed 10 years ago and offers buyers open plan living with double doors leading to a sunny outdoor area. The kitchen is bright and modern. Both bedrooms are generously sized and have robes & ceiling fans. A separate carport takes care of the car accommodation. The lifestyle, companionship & security living here offers will make you wonder why you waited so long to make the move.
"Drysdale Retirement Village"
At Drysdale Retirement Village you'll find a way of life that allows you to do what you want, when you want, within the framework of security and care that residents enjoy. We believe retirement shouldn't be an end to active years.
On the contrary, it's a time to start living!
The Drysdale Retirement Village has been home to so many happy memories since 1984. We hope it will become your new home very soon.
Call or email to inspect this property.

Description:
Serene and Tranquil Entertainers Paradise!
Combine a serene, rural setting, add a dash of character, with a mix of spacious family living and the result is this unique lifestyle property that is like nothing else available on the local market.
Sprawling across a 910m2 parcel and split over 2 levels, this home offers room for the whole family to enjoy and would make a perfect dual occupancy set up. The ground floor comprises an open plan living, dining and fully equipped kitchen with SS appliances and an abundance of storage options. The master retreat and ensuite is also situated on this level, complete with a spacious laundry, separate toilet, and versatile storeroom. Float upstairs and you're welcomed by a spacious 2nd living area and study nook, which offers sliding door access to an expansive alfresco. Bedroom 2 boasts its own private sitting area, with the remaining 3 bedrooms all offering sliding door access to the front balcony and a central family bathroom.
When it comes to outdoor entertaining options, take your pick! With an enviable Northern aspect, unwind and relax with the family in the manicured and private front garden, which is also equipped with an undercover area and an open deck. The back garden offers further options, with an open grassed space, paved area and access via external stairs to the top level alfresco.
Off street parking is no concern here, with dual cross overs and a 6x6m garage with rear access to the secure back garden on offer, perfect for multiple cars, trailers, boats and even the caravan!
A rare opportunity to secure your piece of paradise, with further scope to add your own touches, while being located only a stone's throw to all major amenities.

Description:
DOUBLE BLOCK! POOL AND UNIT! ALL OFFERS CONSIDERED!
Enviable central Drysdale position, loads of space and extra generous proportions here at no. 45. The facade is wrapped by a wide verandah and mature gardens. Enter through the wide ornate front door to a gracious entry hallway and double glass period doors through to the formal lounge room. The spacious kitchen features solid Blackwood timber cabinetry, St George double oven & DW with dining area and second adjacent living room. Three generous bedrooms, BIR'S in main, plus study or fourth bedroom. Central bathroom, shower combined with laundry and separate toilet. Features include period dado, high ceilings, central heating and cooling, space heater, instant gas HWS, as new colorbond roofing, 2 x 30,000lt water tanks and 5 minutes stroll to the centre of Drysdale. The double access allows for 4 vehicles as well as caravan and/or boat space, workshop option. Still plenty of room for the pool with the rambling gardens adding seclusion and privacy. A fantastic central Drysdale property!
